title: 820-3330 missing pm_slp_s4_l
message:
water damaged board, no major corrosion, ran it through the ultrasonic anyway.
First problem with this board was g3h was 1.8V due to q7530 being shorted, after replacing it, g3h is now 12.6 as it should be.
Now i keep going in circles trying to trace down pm_slp_s4_l, i think i have it down to PP3v3_SUS missing, but keep ending up lost or in circles.

title: 820-3330 missing pm_slp_s4_l
message: Q7530 shorted and very likely killed the CPU.

title: 820-3330 missing pm_slp_s4_l
message: i suspected as much. is there something i can do to confirm that?

title: 820-3330 missing pm_slp_s4_l
message: Without putting a good CPU on the board there is no real way. Shorted high side FETs are usually a direct write off for me.
